🧩 Problem: Range Sum Query – Immutable

👉 Given an integer array nums, handle multiple queries:

Return the sum of elements between index left and right (inclusive).

Input:
nums = [1, 2, 3, 4]

Queries:
sumRange(0, 2) → 1 + 2 + 3 = 6
sumRange(1, 3) → 2 + 3 + 4 = 9


Solution:
class NumArray(nums: IntArray) {
    val prefixSum = IntArray(nums.size)
    init{
    prefixSum[0] = nums[0]
      // sum of all index
        for(i in 1 until nums.size){
         prefixSum[i] = nums[i] + prefixSum[i -1] // [1, 3, 6, 10]
        } 
    }

    fun sumRange(left: Int, right: Int): Int {
      // left = 1 , right = 3
        return  if(left == 0){
            prefixSum[right] // if left is 0 cant decrease select the right index value
          }else{
            prefixSum[right] - prefixSum[left - 1] // prefixSum[right] = 10 , prefixSum[left -1] =   1 => 9 (left index index is decreased by 1 to include the index)
          }
    }


}


